@1711 = ~Horn~
@1712 = ~Horn of Blasting~
@1713 = ~This is a small horn. Horns are typically made of bone or metal and can produce a large variety of sounds.~
@1714 = ~While many army engineers spent their time perfecting siege equipment, Julius Baggar delved into magical tomes for his engineering insights. Therein he found ancient scriptures that detailed how to make, control, and wield sound waves. The Horn of Blasting was his first and only attempt at applying the theoretical magical knowledge to the creation of a practical new technology. An apprentice blew through the horn while it was aimed in the direction of Julius, who had insisted on a 'useful experiment.' The resulting shockwave that emanated from the horn first stunned poor Julius, and then tore him apart.

