@2240 = ~Wand of Fear~
@2241 = ~Wands are 1 1/4 feet long and slender. They are made of ivory, bone, or wood and are usually tipped with something - metal, crystal, stone, etc. They are fragile and tend to break easily. Because of this, they are often kept in cases. Wands generally store one or more magical effects powered by charges, each use costing one or more charges (depending in the item). When a wand runs out of charges, it is consumed and destroyed.~
@2242 = ~A Wand of Fear strikes terror into the heart of the target and any creatures within a 30' radius. Opponents within the area must save vs. wand or flee in terror for 5 rounds. This panic is not universal, however, as the stout of heart have been known to resist its magic.

Like all wands, the Wand of Fear can only be used a limited number of times before it is expended. Once these have been used, it shatters.

