@2389 = ~Rod of Lordly Might +3~
@2390 = ~Also called the Wrath of Three Kings, though not associated with any named king in particular, this rod was likely made in 1090DR. It saw use during the Battle of the Bones, but for which side is uncertain as it was found amongst the dead after a larger skirmish. Untransformed, the rod may serve as a powerful club with defensive enchantments, but its true power lies in the seven studlike buttons along its length that unlock the rod's magic. The first four of these buttons extend and transform the rod into alternative forms: a flail of disruption, a flaming long sword, a hypnotic axe, and a spear of speed. The final three buttons, rather than transforming the rod itself, instead activate powerful abilities: the first creates a ghastly spectre of the wielder, terrifying all those who see it; the second completely paralyzes another creature, rendering them helpess when pointed at; and lastly, the third directly sucks at the life of the target, healing the wielder of the rod.

The rod is currently untransformed.

STATISTICS:

